"Dear fellow MIDI guru (which you are if you are reading this ""Info"" page!)

"Thanks for acquiring this MIDI file written by me!  I hope you like it and I would appreciate some feedback.  Please visit my www home page for the latest information on how to contact me:  http://www.geocities.com/southbeach/port/5942\012"
"This MIDI file was written on an Intel Pentium(r) II 266MHz machine with a Creative Labs SoundBlaster(TM) AWE32(TM) sound card
"This MIDI file conforms to the General MIDI (GM) 1.0 formal specifications laid out by the MMA (MIDI Manufacturers Association) which includes Roland Corporation
"The SysEx (system exclusive) messages in this MIDI file set the primary MIDI emulation mode to GM
column6: and for Creative Labs SoundBlaster AWE32/AWE64 cards set the reverb type to ""Hall2"" and the chorus type to ""Chorus4"".\012"

column4: "It is highly recommended that you use the Roland GS subset emulation mode.  This MIDI file has been optimized to use these mode and effects settings.\012"
"In the case where it sounds all weird on your particular MIDI output device
